HEADWORD: margin call
<hw>margin call</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Stock market)</fld> <def>A
demand by a broker that a customer deposit enough to bring his margin up
to the minimum requirement; -- caused by the decline in market prices of
a security or commodity purchased on margin{5}.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> call.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marginella</ent>⟦br⟧
